    "explanation": "For clarity, assume that the ant is in a corner by the ceiling. Denote that corner by A, and denote by B the opposite corner to A, which is by the floor. The shortest path from A to B would require the ant to go on a straight line across a wall of the room toa side of the floor and from there on a straight line along the floor to the B. If you imagine laying down to the floor the vertical wall the ant went down from A to the floor, you have a 10 x 20 rectangle with A and B opposite corners in the rectangle. The shortest path for the ant to go from A to B is by following the diagonal of the rectangle, which has length 10/5 + 22.36. O",
